Judicial.definition: of or relating to a judgment
Judicial.origin: [Latin judicialis , from judicium judgment, from judic- judex judge, from jus right, law + dicere to determine, say]

1 a.definition: of or relating to a judgment, the function of judging, the administration of justice, or the judiciary

sub_terms.b: of, relating to, or being the branch of government that is charged with trying all cases that involve the government and with the administration of justice within its jurisdiction compare,,

2.definition: created, ordered, or enforced by a court [a foreclosure] compare,
